<HEAD>`Seven Underwater Wonders of World' Are Named</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A group of marine experts says the `` seven underwater wonders of the world'' could be lost without a global effort to protect the world's oceans and seas. `` We're killing the oceans,'' said former astronaut <PERSON> Scott </PERSON> <PERSON> Carpenter </PERSON>, one of a panel of experts who named the sites Friday to focus public attention on the world's underwater environment. <PERSON> Rick </PERSON> <PERSON> Sammon </PERSON>, president of the sponsoring organization, CEDAM International, said the selection was the start of an educational campaign aimed at preserving `` the world's beautiful but very fragile marine environment.'' `` If a concerted effort is not undertaken soon to protect and preserve our underwater wonders, they _ like the classic Seven Wonders of the World _ could be lost forever through carelessness, negligence or deliberate mistreatment,'' he said. The seven underwater wonders, selected by the 14-member panel of marine scientists, conservationists and explorers, are: <PERSON> Palau </PERSON>, an island group in <LOCATION> Micronesia </LOCATION>; the northern <LOCATION> Red </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Sea </LOCATION>; the Great Barrier Reef of <LOCATION> Australia </LOCATION>; the waters of the <LOCATION> Galapagos </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Islands </LOCATION> off the coast of <LOCATION> Ecuador </LOCATION>; <LOCATION> Lake </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Baikal </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> Siberia </LOCATION>; the <LOCATION> Belize </LOCATION> Barrier Reef; and the deep ocean vents in the middle of the <LOCATION> Atlantic </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Pacific </LOCATION> oceans. An honorable mention went to whales as one of the great living wonders of the seas. CEDAM International is a non-profit group of 1,000 mostly marine scientists and conservationists based at <LOCATION> Croton-on-Hudson </LOCATION>, N.Y. The educational campaign will include collecting data and publishing information packets about the seven sites, a documentary series, a touring exhibit of underwater photographs, school curricula on marine conservation and an art-quality photo book. <PERSON> Carpenter </PERSON>, an environmental consultant from <LOCATION> Vail </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Colo. </LOCATION>, blamed the world's runaway population for the declining health of the oceans and marine life. `` We've got to stop population growth and we've got to eliminate our ignorance,'' he said. `` The ocean is a very delicate entity and people do n't realize that. Without healthy oceans, a healthy planet is impossible.'' The 13 other panelists included representatives of the <ORGANIZATION> Smithsonian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Institution </ORGANIZATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Geographic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Society </ORGANIZATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nations </ORGANIZATION>, the <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Aquarium </LOCATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Zoological </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Society </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Wildlife </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Conservation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Maryland </ORGANIZATION>, the federal <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Oceanic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Atmospheric </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Administration </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> CSIRO </ORGANIZATION>, <LOCATION> Australia </LOCATION>'s largest scientific and industrial research organization.
