<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Police searched for an 18-year-old suspect and put bulletproof vests on five young white men subjected to death threats after they were charged with participating in a fatal racial attack. The five were charged Friday in the death of <PERSON> Yusef </PERSON> <PERSON> Hawkins </PERSON>, 16, who was shot Wednesday night when he and three friends, all black, went to the mostly white <LOCATION> Bensonhurst </LOCATION> neighborhood of <LOCATION> Brooklyn </LOCATION> to try to buy a used car. Police said <PERSON> Hawkins </PERSON> and his friend ran into a gang of 10 to 30 young people armed with baseball bats and at least one gun in rage against interracial dating. Parallels to the 1986 <PERSON> Howard </PERSON> <PERSON> Beach </PERSON> case deepened as it emerged that one of <PERSON> Hawkins </PERSON>' companions, <PERSON> Luther </PERSON> <PERSON> Sylvester </PERSON>, 17, is a cousin of <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Griffith </PERSON>. <PERSON> Griffith </PERSON> was chased to his death in <LOCATION> Howard </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Beach </LOCATION> by a gang of white teen-agers angry that blacks entered their neighborhood. As condemnation mounted from civil rights leaders and candidates in this year's city elections, police announced a $ 10,000 reward for information leading to other arrests and convictions in the case. The <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Times </ORGANIZATION> and the <ORGANIZATION> Daily </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION> reported in their Saturday editions that witnesses identified an 18-year-old as the gunman and that he was the subject of an intensive manhunt. Officially, police said only that a sixth youth was wanted for questioning. The suspects charged Friday were led out of a police station wearing bulletproof vests. An anonymous caller had told a desk sergeant that `` they were going to get those guys as soon as they left the station,'' Inspector <PERSON> Richard </PE